This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a novel quantization method for deep neural network compression. It also involves experiments on image classification tasks, which are commonly studied in the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper involves techniques for reducing quantization error, which is a common challenge in the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of deep neural networks also suggests a potential fit for the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of weight distributions, which is a common topic in the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
